Package com.cafean.JobStatus.tree

Class CalcServerNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.swing.tree.DefaultMutableTreeNode
      • com.cafean.JobStatus.tree.CalcServerNode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CalcServerClient, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, javax.swing.tree.MutableTreeNode, javax.swing.tree.TreeNode
    public class CalcServerNode
extends javax.swing.tree.DefaultMutableTreeNode
implements CalcServerClient
    An extension of DefaultMutableTreeNode used internally to represent a Calculation Server in a JTree.

      • updateNode

        public boolean updateNode()
        Attempts to update the given CalcServerNode's representation and contents based on it's status and retrieved data from its interface. Updates for CalcServerNodes without connected interfaces are ignored. Updating an CalcServerNode entails retrieving root projects from it's interface with @{link CalcServerIntf#GetProjectInfo GetProjectInfo} and comparing them with the locally stored root project nodes. Projects that are no longer available are then discarded from local data. Any errors occurring during this update will cause this node's interface to die.
        See Also:
        getInterface(), killCalcServer()

      • killCalcServer

        public void killCalcServer()
        Causes an CalcServerNode and its interface object to die. Usually called when an error has occurred during an interface operation. Removes all child nodes and collapses the CalcServerNode. Destroys the interface object and sets the node's state to dead.
